      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: PTP - Procure To Pay
Process Group: PM - Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-050-050 Identify Supplier Rationalization Opportunities</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-964F9BE0-A707-4549-9628-32E18BAF9AB0" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Resource tail supplier spend by transferring business from tail to top suppliers</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-AA05DC7D-D7EC-458F-BDA8-E76F21394E4D" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
               <signavio:dictionaryLink>/glossary/379d0e2ec2f943cab5c10dc3521829f3</signavio:dictionaryLink>
            </signavio:signavioDictionaryLink>
            <signavio:signavioType dataObjectType="IT-System"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bgcolor" metaValue="#e1e1e1"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>SAP Ariba</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-CFBCFF9E-F352-48A1-AC42-4FCB5E7D2F23" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Run Spend reports .</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-C32F946D-3E59-4529-A6F1-957B32B01B5F" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Definition
•Identify ways to reduce the number of suppliers used and buy more items from top suppliers (to generate economies of scale). Typically, pareto analysis of the supply base will show that most purchasing spend is concentrated with a few key suppliers and most suppliers (perhaps 80%) represent the minority of spend (perhaps 20%). There is a high administrative overhead concerned with using and maintaining suppliers on an occasional basis and for low value items. Typical solutions are to reduce the number of suppliers or consider outsourcing opportunities.
Business process supports:
•Risk mitigation by reducing dependency on suppliers with lower spend or uncontracted suppliers in tail spend
•Additional business opportunity for preferred suppliers allowing negotiation leverage.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-F4A05A01-1053-48F5-AFE8-BC34CB5D83DC" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Nageswaran, Rohan &lt;rohan.nageswaran@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
